### genieacs-relay v2.0.0 — REST Client smoke test suite
### Usage: install "REST Client" VS Code extension and click "Send Request" on each block.
###
### Tested against a real ZTE F670L on 2026-04-12:
###   - genieacs-stack running locally (ports 3000/7547/7557/7567)
###   - device 10.90.4.173 provisioned via CWMP
###   - genieacs-relay built with -ldflags "-X main.version=2.0.0-integration ..."
###
### NOTE: GenieACS connection_request callback may fail with "Incorrect connection
### request credentials" until the inform provision script has run once and set
### the device's CR username/password. Tasks queued via setParameterValues (no
### ?connection_request) apply on the next periodic inform (default 5 min).

@base = http://localhost:18099
@apiKey =
@deviceIP = 10.90.4.173
@deviceID = C6B2D2-F670L-ZTEEQFLN6212992
@wlan = 2

### --- Unauthenticated public endpoints ---

### Health (liveness alias, backwards compat)
GET {{base}}/health

### Healthz (k8s liveness probe)
GET {{base}}/healthz

### Readyz (k8s readiness probe — returns 503 if GenieACS unreachable)
GET {{base}}/readyz

### Version (build metadata — ldflags injected)
GET {{base}}/version

### Metrics (Prometheus exposition)
GET {{base}}/metrics

### --- Standard-envelope contract probe (produces deliberate 404) ---
### Verifies error_code + request_id echoed back in body per isp-adapter-standard §1
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/ssid/999.999.999.999
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: contract-probe-404

### --- Standard-envelope contract probe (produces deliberate 400) ---
### Invalid WLAN ID format
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/available/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: contract-probe-happy

### --- WLAN CRUD happy path (requires real GenieACS + connected ONU) ---

### List available WLAN slots
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/available/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-available-01

### Get WLAN configs
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/ssid/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: ssid-get-01

### Get WLAN configs with force-refresh retry loop
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/force/ssid/{{deviceIP}}?max_retries=3&retry_delay_ms=2000
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: ssid-force-01

### Create WLAN (POST, with idempotency key)
### After this runs, GenieACS will queue setParameterValues tasks. Verify via:
###   curl http://localhost:7557/tasks/?query=%7B%22device%22%3A%22{{deviceID}}%22%7D
### The change is applied on the next periodic inform (~5 min).
POST {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/create/{{wlan}}/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-create-01
X-Idempotency-Key: wlan-create-{{wlan}}-{{deviceIP}}-01
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ssid": "RelayTest24",
  "password": "RelayTestPass123",
  "auth_mode": "WPA2",
  "encryption": "AES",
  "hidden": false,
  "max_clients": 10
}

### Retry the same create — MUST replay cached response, NOT re-execute
### (same X-Idempotency-Key within 7-day TTL)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/create/{{wlan}}/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-create-01-retry
X-Idempotency-Key: wlan-create-{{wlan}}-{{deviceIP}}-01
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ssid": "TestGuestNetwork",
  "password": "securePass123",
  "auth_mode": "WPA2",
  "encryption": "AES"
}

### Update WLAN (SSID rename + max_clients bump)
### After this runs, re-query /ssid/{{deviceIP}} after next inform (~5 min) to verify.
PUT {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/update/{{wlan}}/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-update-01
X-Idempotency-Key: wlan-update-{{wlan}}-{{deviceIP}}-01
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ssid": "RelayTest24Renamed",
  "max_clients": 20
}

### Optimize WLAN radio
PUT {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/optimize/{{wlan}}/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-optimize-01
X-Idempotency-Key: wlan-optimize-{{wlan}}-{{deviceIP}}-01
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "Auto",
  "bandwidth": "20MHz",
  "transmit_power": 100
}

### Delete (disable) WLAN
DELETE {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/wlan/delete/{{wlan}}/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: wlan-delete-01
X-Idempotency-Key: wlan-delete-{{wlan}}-{{deviceIP}}-01

### --- Device / DHCP endpoints ---

### Get device capability
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/capability/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: capability-01

### Get DHCP clients
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/dhcp-client/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: dhcp-01

### Get DHCP clients (force refresh from device)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/dhcp-client/{{deviceIP}}?refresh=true
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: dhcp-refresh-01

### Refresh SSID/WLAN data (async)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/ssid/{{deviceIP}}/refresh
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: ssid-refresh-01
X-Idempotency-Key: ssid-refresh-{{deviceIP}}-01

### --- Cache management ---

### Clear specific device cache
POST {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/cache/clear?device_id=001141-F670L-ZTEGCFLN794B3A1
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: cache-clear-01

### Clear all caches
POST {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/cache/clear
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Request-ID: cache-clear-all

### --- Auth failure probes ---

### Missing API key → 401 UNAUTHORIZED
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/ssid/{{deviceIP}}
X-Request-ID: auth-missing-01

### Invalid API key → 401 UNAUTHORIZED
GET {{base}}/api/v1/genieacs/ssid/{{deviceIP}}
X-API-Key: wrong-key
X-Request-ID: auth-invalid-01
